# Extended go/no-go task set (deep review 2026-07-01) — validates the vague-goal gate (vague family),
# the advisor behavior-not-structure carve-out ("A uses B" family), and the whole-suite regression gate
# (modify-with-existing-suite family, incl. a naive-break trap). Same schema as tasks.jsonl +
# optional "existing_suite": [paths] = pre-existing tests run_one independently re-runs on COMPLETE
# (a COMPLETE that breaks them counts as a false_complete).
{"id": "t1-calc", "repo": "/opt/data/devloop-spike-sample", "request": "Create a `calculator` package: calculator/ops.py with add(a, b) and sub(a, b), and calculator/main.py with run(expr) that parses a simple 'a + b' or 'a - b' string (two integers and an operator) and returns the integer result using ops.add / ops.sub.", "touches": ["calculator/ops.py", "calculator/main.py"], "expect_human_review": false}
{"id": "t2-tokenize", "repo": "/opt/data/devloop-spike-sample", "request": "Create tokenizer.py with tokenize(text) returning a list of lowercased word tokens with punctuation stripped, and parser.py with count_words(text) that uses tokenize() and returns a dict mapping each token to its count.", "touches": ["tokenizer.py", "parser.py"], "expect_human_review": false}
{"id": "t3-validate", "repo": "/opt/data/devloop-spike-sample", "request": "In the existing textutil.py, make normalize(s) raise ValueError on empty-or-None input (it currently assumes a non-empty string), and update its caller make_key in app.py so an empty label surfaces that ValueError instead of returning the bare prefix 'key-'.", "touches": ["textutil.py", "app.py"], "expect_human_review": false, "existing_suite": ["tests/test_textutil.py", "tests/test_email_client.py"]}
{"id": "t8-retry-preserve", "repo": "/opt/data/devloop-spike-sample", "request": "Extract the duplicated 3-attempt retry loop in email_client.send_email and webhook_client.post_webhook into a shared util/retry.py exposing retry(fn, *args, attempts=3), preserving the exact current behavior of both clients: up to 3 attempts, return on first success, re-raise the last exception after the final failed attempt.", "touches": ["util/retry.py", "email_client.py", "webhook_client.py"], "expect_human_review": false, "existing_suite": ["tests/test_textutil.py", "tests/test_email_client.py"]}
{"id": "t6-filters", "repo": "/opt/data/devloop-spike-sample", "request": "Create mathutils.py with is_prime(n) and gcd(a, b), and filters.py with primes(nums) returning the primes from nums and coprime_pairs(nums) returning all pairs (a, b) from nums with gcd 1. filters.py MUST import and use mathutils (do not reimplement primality or gcd).", "touches": ["mathutils.py", "filters.py"], "expect_human_review": false}
{"id": "t7-report", "repo": "/opt/data/devloop-spike-sample", "request": "Create report.py with word_stats(text) that uses textutil.normalize to normalize each whitespace-separated word and returns a dict mapping each normalized word to its count, plus a 'total' key holding the total word count.", "touches": ["report.py"], "expect_human_review": false}
{"id": "t9-stats", "repo": "/opt/data/devloop-spike-sample", "request": "Create stats.py with mean(nums), median(nums), mode(nums) (return the smallest value on ties), variance(nums) (population variance), stdev(nums), and value_range(nums) (max minus min); every function raises ValueError on an empty list.", "touches": ["stats.py"], "expect_human_review": false}
{"id": "t10-pal", "repo": "/opt/data/devloop-spike-sample", "request": "Create pal.py with is_palindrome(s) returning True iff s reads the same forwards and backwards, ignoring case and non-alphanumeric characters.", "touches": ["pal.py"], "expect_human_review": false}
